commentary: SW Masakadza to Misbah-ul-Haq, no run slower ball on middle and leg. Misbah fails to connect as he makes room to work it away through the off side. Ahmed makes a dash in anticipation but then sees the bowler pick up the ball to throw down the non-striker's end. Ahmed, who looks as though he is getting in the way of the throw, is able to get in on time. The Zimbabweans go up to appeal the decision, as it looks as though Ahmed was getting in the way, but the umpires finally decree that it is still not out. Interesting one there as it looked blatant.

commentary: Abdur Rehman to Waller, OUT another run-out chance and is he gone? It's gone to the third umpire. It was flatter outside off and they went for the single as soon as Waller pushed it on off. When the bail is dislodged, he looks in, but was out a frame before that. The replays are not very conclusive here and he's been given out! Williams stretched a lot there but looks like it wasn't enough. The third umpire took a long long time and we got a feeling he would be given not out for getting the benefit of the doubt but a brave decision from the umpire
shortText: Abdur Rehman to Waller, OUT
text: another run-out chance and is he gone? It's gone to the third umpire. It was flatter outside off and they went for the single as soon as Waller pushed it on off. When the bail is dislodged, he looks in, but was out a frame before that. The replays are not very conclusive here and he's been given out! Williams stretched a lot there but looks like it wasn't enough. The third umpire took a long long time and we got a feeling he would be given not out for getting the benefit of the doubt but a brave decision from the umpire

commentary: Abdur Rehman to Utseya, OUT Oh mix up there and he's run out! Holds this one back just a touch and the batsman stays at his crease, looking to work it square on the leg side. He can't make any contact as the ball dribbles down to short third man. The batsman sets off for a single but the fielder grabs the ball and throws it back with more than enough time for the keeper to remove the bails. Utseya trudges off and Zimbabwe lose an important wicket

commentary: Abdur Rehman to Panyangara, OUT top edge and Rehman yells a loud 'mine' and takes it safely. Another wicket in the infamous Powerplay. commentary: Saeed Ajmal to Waller, OUT and its all over. Ajmal gives this one a little air and bowling from around the wicket forces Waller to look to clip it into the leg side. The leading edge is taken and Abdur Rehman at point takes the simplest of catches. Pakistan win the deciding ODI and claim the series.
